The governorship election primaries of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) scheduled for Tuesday, January 11, 2022 has been shifted to Wednesday, January 12, 2022. That much was contained in a statement issued by the party’s National Organising Secretary, Umar Bature, yesterday.   Another Nigerian killed in South Africa     NDLEA boss Marwa loses first wife, Zainab     IPAC wrong on direct primary   Bature, in the statement titled ‘PDP shifts screening of Osun governorship aspirants to Wednesday, January 12’, said the screening exercise would take place in the same venue: the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja at 10:00 am. “The PDP regrets any inconveniences the change in date may have caused. All aspirants, leaders, critical stakeholders and members of our party in Osun state should take note and by this, be guided accordingly,” the statement read